      "error_message": "Sidecar-side changes (image fix, CACHE_VERSION bump) never reached the running IDE despite rebuilds; runtime/0.1.0/main.js stayed stale",
      "file": "plugin/src/main/kotlin/com/aicoach/jetbrains/sidecar/SidecarRuntime.kt",
      "root_cause": "ensureExtracted (commit 3be5121) detected 'dev sandbox' via getResource('/sidecar/main.js').protocol=='file' and only then skipped the isComplete() short-circuit. But the IntelliJ runIde sandbox packages the plugin as plugin-0.1.0.jar, so the protocol is 'jar', inDevSandbox=false, isComplete(stale files)=true -> the first-ever extraction was reused forever. Version string (0.1.0) never changes between dev builds. Webview app.js was unaffected (served from JAR by AssetSchemeHandler, not extracted), which masked the bug \u2014 only sidecar main.js changes silently failed to load.",
      "fix": "Replaced the file://-vs-jar:// heuristic with a content fingerprint: hash the bundled /sidecar/main.js (SHA-256), store it as runtime/<ver>/.bundle-hash, and re-extract whenever the extraction is incomplete or the stored hash != current. Correct for dev (rebuilt bundle) and prod (plugin update) regardless of version-dir name. Verified: fresh runIde re-extracted main.js with the fix and cache re-parsed to version 10.",
