      "timestamp": "2026-06-15T18:30:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "Dashboard stuck on 'Building Activity Index' spinner after a theme change (open/close works, theme switch hangs)",
      "file": "plugin/src/main/kotlin/com/aicoach/jetbrains/theme/WebviewThemeSync.kt",
      "root_cause": "WebviewThemeSync called browser.cefBrowser.reload() on theme change. The webview waits for the sidecar's one-shot 'dataReady' push before fetching/rendering. dataReady is sent once per sidecar connection (on first parse). A soft reload restarts app.js on the SAME bridge/connection, so the sidecar never re-emits dataReady \u2014 the reloaded page waits forever. (A close/reopen makes a NEW connection, which re-handshakes and re-emits dataReady, which is why open/close worked.)",
      "fix": "Removed the soft reload (and the load-gate/second load handler) from WebviewThemeSync. Theme changes now do live :root CSS-variable injection only (executeJavaScript setProperty) \u2014 the whole CSS UI recolors instantly with no reload, so nothing hangs. Chart.js (colors captured at mount) fully recolors when the tool window is reopened.",
